  "prompt": "How much does an Olympic gold medal cost?",
  "response": "The cost of an Olympic gold medal can vary depending on the specific games and the fluctuating prices of materials used. As of recent Olympics, the gold medals are made primarily of silver and coated with a thin layer of pure gold. Specifically, a typical Olympic gold medal contains around 6 grams of gold plating over approximately 550 grams of silver.\n\nTo estimate the cost:\n\n1. The price of gold per gram varies but is roughly around $60-$70 USD.\n2. The price of silver per gram is around $0.70-$1 USD.\n\nTherefore, the gold component (6 grams x $60) would be about $360, and the silver component (550 grams x $0.70) would be around $385. Combining these, the material cost of an Olympic gold medal can be estimated to be around $745, with fluctuations based on current market prices.\n\nIt's important to note that this estimate does not account for manufacturing costs, design, labor, and other factors involved in the creation of the medals, which could increase the overall cost.",
